<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-895-418  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 895 418.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Data Communications  Oct 1989 v18 n13 p68(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Samson shears Southern Bell. (Barbara Samson, founder ofIntermedia Communications Inc., which runs a fiber-optic networkin Orlando, FL) (Industry Watch) (company profile)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mulqueen, John T.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Barbara Samson, founder of Intermedia Communications Inc,discovered soon after graduating from college in 1986 that whatbusinesses wanted was good local telecommunications services, andthat they had enough long-distance alternatives.andP;  IntermediaCommunications now runs a fiber-optic network in Orlando, FL, andis developing another one in Tampa; the company plans to move intoMiami and St. Petersburg in 1989 and to Jacksonville in 1990.andO;Samson serves as VP for external affairs, handling regulatoryaffairs, public relations and other marketing activities; amongthe company's clients are Ford Motor Co, IBM, Anchor Glass andGeneral Mills Inc. DS-0, DS-1 and DS-3 dedicated-line service issold by the company, principally for connecting to long-distancecarriers.andP;  Intermedia has caused Southern Bell and GTE FloridaTelephone, the two local exchange companies, to cut T1 rates.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Intermedia Communications of Florida Inc. (officials andemployees).andO;Topic:     T1 CommunicationsCommunications Service SuppliersFloridaCompetitionTelecommunicationsTelephone companies.andO;Person:    Samson, Barbara (management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>